    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-01-23T18:17:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-23T18:17:00-05:00" n="532"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d532">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/1–2252: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        United States Representative at the United Nations</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Austin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-01-23T18:17:00-05:00"
                            >January 23, 1952—6:17 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Gadel2">Gadel</gloss> 808. Re <gloss target="#t_Delga1"
                        >Delga</gloss> 1143<note n="1" xml:id="d532fn1">Dated January 22, <hi
                            rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> Oatis case. View considerations <gloss
                        target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> agrees Del opinion not feasible secure
                    adoption res Oatis case. Sufficient make strong ref Oatis in statement re
                    pertinent Sec <gloss target="#t_ECOSOC1">ECOSOC</gloss> Report. However view
                    obvious importance of issue and in absence submission res <gloss
                        target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> stresses importance adequate US statement
                    along lines special text of statement re Oatis transmitted to Del by <gloss
                        target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> in memo Dec. 11 to Green and Simsarian.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d532fn2">Memorandum not found in Department of State files.
                        James F. Green and James Simsarian were Advisers on the United States
                        Delegation, and both were engaged in Committee Three matters.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> still hopes Del able persuade other Dels
                    make appropriate supporting statement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
